      <body>
         <div type="edition" ana="#b1" xml:lang="grc" subtype="transcription" xml:id="elus0039.transcription" corresp="#elus0039.translation">
            <p>
               <gap reason="illegible" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
               <gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="character"/>
               <orig>Σ</orig>
               <expan>
                  <abbr>
                     <supplied reason="lost">ἀ</supplied>
                     <lb break="no"/>θά</abbr>
                  <ex>να</ex>
                  <abbr>τος</abbr>
               </expan>. <lb/>
               <unclear>ἔ</unclear>τους <num value="321">τκα</num>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" ana="#b1" xml:id="elus0039.translation" corresp="#elus0039.transcription">
            <p>...(No one is) immortal. Year 321</p>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>The letters 'να' in the word θάνατος, on the second line, were originally left out, and were added below. 321 in the Arabian era corresponds to 426-427 CE.</p>
         </div>
